svn - central version control system
git - distributrd version control system

Cental VCS:
if server is offline then all you have access is the checked out files and if something happens to the remote repo then there better be a backup or else the entire data is gone
One central VCS that everybody accesses and uses.


Distributed VCS:
everybody has a local repo that has all info as the remote repo and is updated evrytime you sync it;
you also have option to have to central vcs if you want it;


